fields.description:
As we talked recently at AtlasCamp (with James H.) we heavily use Javascript objects from GH realm to deliver functionality of our Agile Cards for JIRA plugin (as of 2.1 it can print issues: cards, columns, all, sprints from GH Boards).

So the things we would love to have (and currently need to hack) are:

1) pluggable (web-item) Tools menu
2) pluggable (web-item) operations on columns in the board
3) pluggable (web-item) operations on the Sprint planning marker
4) stable Javascript API for accessing cards (also currently selected) and the boards. See below for more details.

BTW:
we had to deliver different fixes/workaround for _each_ new GH version between GH 6.0 and 6.0.3 (so 6.0.1 and 6.0.2 too) as in each of these minor versions JS changed slightly causing our plugin to blow off.

We use the following unofficial GH Javascript stuff (notes from our developer):

{quote}

// Spartez AgileCards 2.1.3 javaScript Grennhopper dependencies--

//
// DOM
//

// Board mode [plan/work/report]
GH.RapidBoard.State.getMode();

// Selected issue keys (array)
GH.RapidBoard.State.getBoardSetting(null,'backlog.selectedIssues'); // plan mode
GH.RapidBoard.State.getBoardSetting(null,'work.selectedIssues'); // work mode

// User specified board name
GH.PlanController.rapidViewData.name;

// User specified sprint name by sprintId
GH.BacklogModel.getOpenSprints(); // :-/ could be better - I must use foreach() to get correct name by id

// Active sprint issue list (array)
GH.BacklogModel.getIssueListForSprint(sprintId).data.visibleIssues; //GH 6.0.1-6.0.2
GH.BacklogModel.getIssueListForSprint(sprintId).data.visibleIssueKeys.toArray(); //GH 6.0.3
// It would be nice if there was a similar function for planned sprints

// Rapid board work mode column name
GH.RapidBoard.RapidListDataController.getColumnById(columnId).name; //GH 5.8.7
GH.GridDataController.model.data.columns; // :-/ I want back GH 5.8.7 function

// Issue keys by columnId
GH.GridDataController.model.data.columnIssueMapping[columnId];


//
// Overriden functions to add UI elements (we call our functions after the following)
// It would be nice if there was an events after refresh page content
//

// to add dropdown menu item
GH.ViewActions.renderOnRapidBoard();

// to add print active sprint icons
GH.BacklogView.draw();
GH.BacklogView.updateOpenSprint();

// to add print planned sprint icons
GH.BacklogView.renderBacklog();
GH.BacklogView.updateSingleMarker();

// to add print column icons in work mode
GH.SwimlaneView.show();
GH.RapidBoard.SwimlaneView.show();



//
// Used HTML objects
//

// dropdown menu
AJS.$("#js-view-actions-list");

// Active sprints
AJS.$(".ghx-sprint-active");
AJS.$(".ghx-sprint-active").attr("data-sprint-id");
	..(".ghx-headline").append(link);

// Planned sprints
AJS.$(".ghx-planned-sprint-container");
AJS.$(".ghx-planned-sprint-container").attr("data-marker-id");
	..(".ghx-controls").append(link);

// Work columns
AJS.$("#ghx-column-headers .ghx-column");
AJS.$("#ghx-column-headers .ghx-column").attr("data-id");
	..(".ghx-column").prepend(link);
{quote}

Any feedback on how to remove some of these unofficial calls or when it will be incorporated in UI would be much appreciated.

